=Episode 14=

24
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,800
It's still here.

25
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:52,720
Zhongliang.

26
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,600
Turn yourself in.

27
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:03,880
Nana.

28
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,120
What did you say?

29
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:09,560
Turn yourself in.

30
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,480
Are you trying to get me to prison

31
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,240
so you'll never see me again, right?

32
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,560
No, Zhongliang.

33
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:20,760
I... I won't.

34
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,000
You're the baby's father.

35
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,680
- Action.
- You're lying.

36
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,880
Now even you want
to abandon me, don't you?

37
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,120
No.

38
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,440
Give me the child.

39
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:36,720
Give me the child!

40
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,160
Give me the child.

41
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:42,640
- Luo Zhongliang!
- Chase him.

42
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:45,920
Luo Zhongliang!

43
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,160
Luo Zhongliang, stop!

44
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,440
- Where are you going?
- Don't come near me.

45
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:50,520
Give the child back to me.

46
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,360
- Where are you going?
- Don't come near me.

47
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,560
Luo Zhongliang, calm down.

48
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,480
I can't live without the child.

49
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,720
Calm down.

50
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:57,040
Calm down.

51
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,040
Nana.

52
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,560
- My child.
- Nana.

53
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,640
My child.

54
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,520
- Calm down.
- You all lie to me.

55
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:05,190
You're all lying to me!

56
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,640
My child!

57
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,560
He went inside.

58
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:24,920
Don't come over.

59
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,120
Luo Zhongliang.

60
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:28,040
(Police)
Let's have a talk.

61
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:31,680
Look, we're old acquaintances.

62
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,640
I watched him be born.

63
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:34,560
Remember?

64
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:41,920
Captain Ye.

65
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:43,960
You're a good person.

66
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,320
So are you.

67
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,600
You just got your wires crossed.

68
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,200
You don't understand.

69
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,160
None of you understand.

70
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,080
I do.

71
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,920
You've lived a wandering life,

72
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,440
and that makes you feel very insecure.

73
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:02,920
You felt very lonely.

74
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,720
But you never hurt others.

75
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,040
Your biggest demand

76
00:04:08,410 --> 00:04:10,680
is to have a safe and warm home.

77
00:04:11,740 --> 00:04:12,880
Am I right?

78
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,480
I know

79
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:23,280
how important this home is to you.

80
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,760
And I believe in your selfless love for baby.

81
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,560
Look, it's too windy
up here on the rooftop.

82
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:33,200
The baby is too young to bear it.

83
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,840
Let's go downstairs and talk.

84
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,240
If

85
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,160
I can never have it,

86
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,400
my life might just be like this.

87
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,400
But now that I finally got it,

88
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,560
I'm still about to lose it.

89
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,480
I really wish

90
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:59,000
I had never had any of this.

91
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:05,840
My dream is to have a complete family.

92
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,560
I absolutely can't lose it.

93
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,200
Today,

94
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,000
right here

95
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,320
is the best place

96
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,400
for our family to find peace.

97
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,640
I know what you're going to do,

98
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,680
Luo Zhongliang.

99
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,600
You can choose to stay and watch

100
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,040
your child grow up day by day.

101
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,000
You can give him love,

102
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,440
warmth, and joy.

103
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,480
You'll be a great father.

104
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:41,960
Just look at

105
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:43,800
how cute he is.

106
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,240
He'll have a different life.

107
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:49,960
He'll grow up in a warm home,

108
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:51,600
and no one will abandon him.

109
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,520
Captain Ye.

110
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,920
I once

111
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:12,700
abandoned my own child.

112
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:14,870
What?

113
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,080
It was me.

114
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,720
I handed him over
to the human trafficker

115
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,800
with my own hands.

116
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,040
Find him a good family.

117
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,000
Forget it.

118
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,280
I won't sell this child.

119
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,280
Give me the child.

120
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,760
I won't sell this child anymore.

121
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,400
Give me the child!

122
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,320
Give...

123
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,120
Give me the child.

124
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:50,560
Luo Zhongliang, what happened?

125
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,360
My child...

126
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,680
My child was taken away.

127
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,960
We'll talk about this later.

128
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,400
Can you

129
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,120
give me the child now?

130
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,040
Look how much he's crying.

131
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,560
I have more experience than you.

132
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,320
Can I come over?

133
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,240
Captain Ye,

134
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,080
maybe you're right.

135
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,960
He might have a different life.

136
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,360
(Luo Zhongliang abandoned his own child)

137
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:30,080
(and his subsequent actions)

138
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:33,320
(have violated China's Criminal Law.)

139
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:35,760
(He will be punished
according to the law.)

140
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:44,060
(Suspect: Luo Zhongliang)

141
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,360
Captain.

142
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,440
Captain, haven't you eaten yet?

143
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,450
I've brought you food.

144
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,480
Thanks.

145
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,520
Let's chat a bit.

146
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,640
Okay.

147
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,240
I was just thinking,

148
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,480
as a man with

149
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,880
severe depression patient,

150
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:06,960
what kind of pressure

151
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,600
could have made
Luo Zhongliang like this?

152
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,400
Lack of understanding, care,
and encouragement.

153
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,120
So he lost

154
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:15,280
the courage to keep going.

155
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:17,840
Yes.

156
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:20,360
People with severe depression

157
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:21,980
are usually very sensitive

158
00:09:21,990 --> 00:09:22,960
and fragile.

159
00:09:23,070 --> 00:09:23,920
Sometimes just a few words

160
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,640
can worsen their condition.

161
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:28,520
That's why they need
the people around them

162
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:30,120
to be tolerant of their harshness

163
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:32,040
and their excessive perfectionism,

164
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:33,240
and forgive

165
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,320
their occasional negative emotions.

166
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:38,440
So,

167
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,160
they really need

168
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,880
patience, tolerance,

169
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,320
and care.

170
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:44,880
If Li Na

171
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,840
had been a bit more caring
and tolerant towards him,

172
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,960
he wouldn't have ended up like that.

173
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,240
Yeah,

174
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,680
it's easier said than done.

175
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:09,180
(Emergency Response Training Base)

176
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,960
Begin.

177
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,060
- Dodge.
- Stop it.

178
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,640
Captain Ye,

179
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,240
do we need to hold back the members

180
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:54,350
of Raptor Commandos?

181
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:56,840
Who are you looking down on?

182
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:11,840
Get out of the way!

183
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:35,780
(How Can a Man Speak
to Make a Woman Listen)

184
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,160
Didn't I ask you to look for information?

185
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,240
What are you doing here?

186
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:45,320
I did.

187
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:47,360
Captain Zhu,

188
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,360
I've noticed

189
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:50,520
something off about you lately.

190
00:12:50,890 --> 00:12:52,200
Don't talk nonsense.

191
00:12:52,310 --> 00:12:53,240
Just do your job.

192
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,760
What book are you reading?

193
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,680
Li Baojun!

194
00:12:59,050 --> 00:12:59,960
Attention!

195
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:00,960
Yes.

196
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:01,920
What do you want to say?

197
00:13:01,980 --> 00:13:02,840
If nothing, get lost.

198
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:03,840
There's something.

199
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,240
What is it?

200
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,640
Today, someone reported drug use.

201
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,440
When Chen and I arrived at the scene,

202
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,040
we found the person
frothing at the mouth

203
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:11,880
and convulsing all over.

204
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:13,000
Luckily he got
to the hospital in time,

205
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,000
so nothing serious happened.

206
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:14,960
Where's he now?

207
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,160
Chen is interrogating him now.

208
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:17,840
Why didn't you say that earlier?

209
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:23,780
(How Can a Man Speak
to Make a Woman Listen)

210
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,520
Mad Dog.

211
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,560
How's it going?

212
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,840
I didn't call you. Why are you here?

213
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:36,720
What's wrong?

214
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,720
Can't I just come to check things out?

215
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:40,280
But you

216
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,940
didn't answer my call.

217
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,600
I thought something had happened to you.

218
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,240
I need to focus on my work, okay?

219
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,020
You've got principles.

220
00:14:54,670 --> 00:14:56,440
Let me tell you, the goods you handled

221
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:57,960
can't be sold at a good price.

222
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,640
Just stop the act.

223
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,640
I can only make the junk

224
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,960
you gave me this way.

225
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,600
It's good enough
to have something to sell.

226
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:05,730
What else are you thinking?

227
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,120
Alright,

228
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:14,760
I know a place.

229
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,680
I'll take you there to check it out.

230
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:23,800
Captain Zhu,

231
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,760
after Xiahou Xiong's gang was taken down,

232
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,360
things were calm for a while.

233
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,720
Now they're dealing drugs again.

234
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,840
Do you think if Wu hadn't died,

235
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,360
he might be involved in this?

236
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:34,600
Hard to say.

237
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:35,720
But

238
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,040
since they're making moves,

239
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,080
there must be some clues.

240
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:40,800
Captain Zhu,

241
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:41,760
the lab report is out.

242
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:42,600
Take a look.

243
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,040
Is it the same as what
we confiscated before?

244
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:45,280
Not at all.

245
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,510
The formula is a mess,
the purity is very low,

246
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,660
and the craftsmanship is poor.

247
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,440
That's why he reacted so strongly

248
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,670
when we caught him.

249
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,080
So it's not the goods from Wu.

250
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:56,920
A folk formula.

251
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:58,440
This indicates

252
00:15:59,590 --> 00:16:00,880
there's local drug manufacturing.

253
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,280
Ye Zhen,

254
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:15,920
we can't keep living in the past.

255
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:20,200
We should say goodbye to him by now.

256
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,720
Why not let yourself go?

257
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:24,760
They really need

258
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:25,760
patience,

259
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:26,680
tolerance,

260
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:27,600
and care.

261
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,360
If Li Na

262
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:32,240
had been a bit more caring
and tolerant towards him,

263
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,480
he wouldn't have ended up like that.

264
00:16:45,420 --> 00:16:48,940
(Zhu Huaiyang)

265
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,140
(Zhu Huaiyang)

266
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:01,680
Hello.

267
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:04,440
Ye Zhen, I heard about
what happened today.

268
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,390
How are you?

269
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:07,780
I'm fine, don't worry.

270
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,060
Haven't you gone home yet?

271
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,770
We got some leads,

272
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:13,160
so we're heading to the bar street.

273
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:14,560
Be careful then,

274
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,080
and get some rest early.

275
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:17,000
You too.

276
00:17:17,510 --> 00:17:18,480
Huaiyang.

277
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:19,520
What's up?

278
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,800
Tomorrow is

279
00:17:22,390 --> 00:17:23,480
our day off.

280
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:27,120
What do you plan to cook for me?

281
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:29,640
What do you feel like eating?

282
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:33,120
Beef noodles.

283
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:35,360
Sure, I'll make them for you.

284
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:36,840
Okay,

285
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:38,140
bye.

286
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,000
Bye-bye.

287
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,320
Captain Zhu.

288
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:25,600
Hello.

289
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,920
Hello, hello, hello.

290
